Let $P = (t,t,t).$  Then lines $CP$ and $AB$ are perpendicular, so their respective vectors are orthgonal.  Hence,
\[\begin{pmatrix} t \\ t \\ t - 1 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ 1 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix} = 0.\]Then $(t)(1) + (t)(1) + (t - 1)(1) = 0.$  Solving, we find $t = \frac{1}{3}.$

Then $P = \left( \frac{1}{3}, \frac{1}{3}, \frac{1}{3} \right),$ and so $CP = \boxed{\frac{\sqrt{6}}{3}}.$

